author: Nexcell Pride
text:
Passed exactly 1 year about that New Live2D reveal.
It's part of her Live2D 2.0, precisely due to same modeler.

Tou Ilie made a great work on modeling... Starting with the New Year outfit at 2020 January 4th and Live2D 2.0 at mid February 2020.
At that moment, despite that new outfit and new hair color, also can described as part of Live2D 2.0 due to same features, but called New Live2D due to new add-ons, like glasses, alternating hairstyle and also a Yandere-mode (that feature couldn't be added at normal Live2D 2.0. Maybe Yasuyuki-sensei was too busy to add them at that moment to add these new features at normal Live2D 2.0)

Curiously and personally talking, I was thinking about it would be her definitive form at following streams, but starting at July 7th she started to alternate between Live2D 2.0 and New Live2D models. Starting September 2020, Rushia used more the Live2D 2.0 (Green haired) than her New Live2D (White and Pink-purple haired)

Fortunately, her Green haired form and the White Pink-purple haired form are part of her cat form at New Live2D 3.0, also modeled by Tou Ilie (Debuted at her 2021's Birthday. The Live2D 3.0 included Live2D's Piyoko)
